{
  "texts": [
    "Both studies were conducted using student samples, highlighting the need to extend these investigations to a more diverse general population.",
    "With large language models (LLMs) showing promise in addressing various mental health concerns 19, 25, it is crucial to explore their capabilities for detecting and measuring social anxiety symptoms specifically.",
    "Like many prior studies, we will use self-report measures as our ground truth.",
    "Our methodology will focus on an interviewbased format with open-ended questions about social anxiety symptoms, encouraging participants to produce free speech.",
    "This approach allows for an analysis of linguistic differences between individuals with and without social anxiety disorder (SAD)."
  ]
}